{"id":4444,"date":"2016-01-21T05:31:25","date_gmt":"2016-01-21T11:31:25","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/new_packaging_for_mcdonalds_by_boxer.php"},"modified":"2016-01-21T05:31:25","modified_gmt":"2016-01-21T11:31:25","slug":"new_packaging_for_mcdonalds_by_boxer","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/new_packaging_for_mcdonalds_by_boxer.php","title":{"rendered":"New Packaging for McDonald&apos;s by Boxer"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Established in 1940, <a href=\"http:\/\/www.mcdonalds.com\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">McDonald&#8217;s<\/a> needs little introduction but to cover the basics: McDonald&#8217;s is a &#8220;global foodservice retailer with over 36,000 locations serving nearly 69 million customers in over 100 countries each day.&#8221; (<em>Each<\/em> day.) This month, McDonald&#8217;s is rolling out new packaging that will be in every location by the end of the year. <a href=\"http:\/\/adage.com\/article\/design\/mcdonald-s-packaging-a-2016-makeover\/302019\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">AdAge reports<\/a> that the design was the result of a week-long design blitz with one designer from each of its lead agency partners &mdash; Leo Burnett Germany, TBWA U.S., DDB Hong Kong, Creata Australia, Boxer UK, Landini Australia, and Forpeople UK &mdash; and the results later turned over to <a href=\"http:\/\/www.boxerbranddesign.com\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Boxer<\/a> for full development and implementation.<\/p>\n<!--more--><blockquote>Starting this month, McDonald&#8217;s restaurants in the United States will unveil new carry-out bags, fountain beverage cups and sandwich boxes.  The new look is simple, fresh and consistent with the company&#8217;s vision to be a modern and progressive burger company.  The new packaging rollout will expand worldwide to 36,000+ restaurants throughout 2016.<\/blockquote><h3><a href=\"http:\/\/news.mcdonalds.com\/Corporate\/Feature-Stories-Articles\/2016\/A-New-Year-and-A-New-Look-for-McDonald-s-Global-Pa\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">McDonald&#8217;s press release<\/a><\/h3>\n<figure class=\"full\">\n<img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/mcdonalds_2016_packaging_evolution.jpg\" alt=\"New Packaging for McDonald&amp;apos;s by Boxer\" \/>\n<figcaption>Packaging evolution over the decades. Um, can we go back to the 1980s one?<\/figcaption>\n<\/figure>\n<blockquote>The designs feature colors that almost sound like the names of new McDonald&#8217;s smoothies or fancy burgers: Passionate Purple, Optimistic Orange, Ocean Fresh Blue, Zesty Lime and Magical Magenta. Of course, McDonald&#8217;s signature red and yellow also appear.<\/blockquote><h3><a href=\"http:\/\/adage.com\/article\/design\/mcdonald-s-packaging-a-2016-makeover\/302019\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">AdAge story<\/a><\/h3>\n<figure class=\"full\">\n<img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/mcdonalds_2016_packaging.jpg\" alt=\"New Packaging for McDonald&amp;apos;s by Boxer\" \/>\n<figcaption>Packaging line-up.<\/figcaption>\n<\/figure>\n<p>The packaging shown in the &#8220;before&#8221; image is the current reality for some McDonald&#8217;s eaters but others may be seeing some other version. Based on browsing the #mcdonalds hashtag on Instagram it seemed the image I chose is the most prevalent design in use. I have no idea, really, as I haven&#8217;t eaten at a McDonald&#8217;s in at least 15 years. But the lack of clarity about what the prevailing packaging is is a reason good enough to change.<\/p>\n<p>The new look is being touted (<a href=\"https:\/\/www.creativereview.co.uk\/cr-blog\/2016\/january\/mcdonalds-has-announced-new-look-stripped-back-packaging-heres-what-makes-it-interesting\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">and celebrated<\/a>) as daring in its committee approach and bold in its execution. Give me a single agency any day of the week and a &#8220;bold&#8221; design that doesn&#8217;t rely on blowing Helvetica 500% and I&#8217;ll be happy, thank you. The design stands out, for sure, because it&#8217;s so different from what McDonald&#8217;s its competition has ever done. (Pro tip: probably for a good reason). At the same time it rides the wave of simplicity and stripping major brands to its bare bones. But this is rudimentary design at best trying to pass as iconic. The focus on &#8220;on&#8221; when exploding the McDonald&#8217;s wordmark on the bags is very confusing and extremely unappealing. There is nothing &#8220;on&#8221; about McDonald&#8217;s and, mostly, it just seems a very weird word to place so much emphasis, um, on.<\/p>\n<figure class=\"full\">\n<img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/mcdonalds_2016_takeout_bag.jpg\" alt=\"New Packaging for McDonald&amp;apos;s by Boxer\" \/>\n<figcaption>Take-out bag.<\/figcaption>\n<\/figure>\n<figure class=\"full\">\n<img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/mcdonalds_2016_takeout_bag_glowing.jpg\" alt=\"New Packaging for McDonald&amp;apos;s by Boxer\" \/>\n<figcaption>Take-out bag, glowing, natch.<\/figcaption>\n<\/figure>\n<figure class=\"full\">\n<img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/mcdonalds_2016_cups.jpg\" alt=\"New Packaging for McDonald&amp;apos;s by Boxer\" \/>\n<figcaption>Cups.<\/figcaption>\n<\/figure>\n<figure class=\"full\">\n<img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/mcdonalds_2016_fashion_box.jpg\" alt=\"New Packaging for McDonald&amp;apos;s by Boxer\" \/>\n<hr \/>\n<img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/mcdonalds_2016_fashion_bag.jpg\" alt=\"New Packaging for McDonald&amp;apos;s by Boxer\" \/>\n<figcaption>&#8220;Couture collection&#8221; promos done in collaboration by current student Pablo Machado and recent graduate Ricardo Hardouin of Miami International University of Art and Design.<\/figcaption>\n<\/figure>\n<figure class=\"full\">\n<img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/mcdonalds_2016_holiday_image.jpg\" alt=\"New Packaging for McDonald&amp;apos;s by Boxer\" \/>\n<figcaption>Holiday promo image using the bags.<\/figcaption>\n<\/figure>\n<p>Here are some shots of the packaging in the wild, to get a <em>real<\/em> sense of how they look:<\/p>\n<blockquote class=\"instagram-media\" data-instgrm-captioned data-instgrm-version=\"6\" style=\"float:left; background:#FFF; border:0; border-radius:3px; box-shadow:0 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.5),0 1px 10px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.15); margin: 1px 1.75% 35px 1px; padding:0; max-width:48%; width:99.375%; width:-webkit-calc(100% - 2px); width:calc(100% - 2px);\"><div style=\"padding:8px;\"> <div style=\" background:#F8F8F8; line-height:0; margin-top:40px; padding:50.0% 0; text-align:center; width:100%;\"> <div style=\" background:url(data:image\/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAACwAAAAsCAMAAAApWqozAAAAGFBMVEUiIiI9PT0eHh4gIB4hIBkcHBwcHBwcHBydr+JQAAAACHRSTlMABA4YHyQsM5jtaMwAAADfSURBVDjL7ZVBEgMhCAQBAf\/\/42xcNbpAqakcM0ftUmFAAIBE81IqBJdS3lS6zs3bIpB9WED3YYXFPmHRfT8sgyrCP1x8uEUxLMzNWElFOYCV6mHWWwMzdPEKHlhLw7NWJqkHc4uIZphavDzA2JPzUDsBZziNae2S6owH8xPmX8G7zzgKEOPUoYHvGz1TBCxMkd3kwNVbU0gKHkx+iZILf77IofhrY1nYFnB\/lQPb79drWOyJVa\/DAvg9B\/rLB4cC+Nqgdz\/TvBbBnr6GBReqn\/nRmDgaQEej7WhonozjF+Y2I\/fZou\/qAAAAAElFTkSuQmCC); display:block; height:44px; margin:0 auto -44px; position:relative; top:-22px; width:44px;\"><\/div><\/div> <p style=\" margin:8px 0 0 0; padding:0 4px;\"> <a href=\"https:\/\/www.instagram.com\/p\/BAx0q7vDxlJ\/\" style=\" color:#000; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:17px; text-decoration:none; word-wrap:break-word;\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">thanks mom ? #mcdonalds ??<\/a><\/p> <p style=\" color:#c9c8cd; font-family